(126, 1, '2018-11-22 11:12:28', '2018-11-22 11:12:28', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A chief of police, also known as police chief or sometimes shortened to just chief, is the title typically given to the top official in the chain of command of a police department, particularly in North America. Alternate titles for this position include police commissioner, colonel (in the Rhode Island State Police), police superintendent, police president, and chief constable</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Ivar Otmar', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ivar-otmar', '', '', '2018-11-22 11:12:28', '2018-11-22 11:12:28', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/townpress-content/?post_type=lsvr_person&amp;p=126', 0, 'lsvr_person', '', 0),
